how to make a menu of insert, display, update and search using c++

To create a menu of insert, display, update, and search options using C++, you can use a combination of functions and a loop to continuously prompt the user for their choice and execute the corresponding functionality. Here's an example code snippet:

#include <iostream>

void insertData() {
    // Code to insert data
    std::cout << "Inserting data..." << std::endl;
}

void displayData() {
    // Code to display data
    std::cout << "Displaying data..." << std::endl;
}

void updateData() {
    // Code to update data
    std::cout << "Updating data..." << std::endl;
}

void searchData() {
    // Code to search data
    std::cout << "Searching data..." << std::endl;
}

int main() {
    int choice;

    do {
        // Display menu options
        std::cout << "Menu:" << std::endl;
        std::cout << "1. Insert" << std::endl;
        std::cout << "2. Display" << std::endl;
        std::cout << "3. Update" << std::endl;
        std::cout << "4. Search" << std::endl;
        std::cout << "0. Exit" << std::endl;

        // Get user's choice
        std::cout << "Enter your choice: ";
        std::cin >> choice;

        // Execute corresponding functionality based on user's choice
        switch (choice) {
            case 1:
                insertData();
                break;
            case 2:
                displayData();
                break;
            case 3:
                updateData();
                break;
            case 4:
                searchData();
                break;
            case 0:
                std::cout << "Exiting..." << std::endl;
                break;
            default:
                std::cout << "Invalid choice! Please try again." << std::endl;
                break;
        }
    } while (choice != 0);

    return 0;
}
In this example, the main() function contains a do-while loop that repeatedly displays the menu options and prompts the user for their choice. The switch statement is used to execute the corresponding function based on the user's choice. The loop continues until the user chooses to exit by entering 0.

You can customize the functions insertData(), displayData(), updateData(), and searchData() to implement the specific functionality you desire for each menu option.

